{"lemma":"عُقْبِ","slug":"عُقْبِ","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عُقْب","root":"عقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n29831","n29832","n29833","n29834","n29835"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%82%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heel","tags":["feminine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"end","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandson","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"offspring, progeny","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"subsequent to, following"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to follow, to succeed, to come after"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to follow, to succeed; to ensue, to pursue, to trail, to tail; to return to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to comment, to revise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"end, latter part, consequence, result, issue, butt, that wherewith one is left","examples":[{"text":"هُنَالِكَ ٱلْوَلَايَةُ لِلّٰهِ ٱلْحَقِّ هُوَ خَيْرٌ ثَوَابًا وَخَيْرٌ عُقْبًا","english":"At this time, support comes ˹only˺ from Allah—the True ˹Lord˺. He is best in reward and best in outcome."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew עָקֵב (ʿāqēḇ, “heel”)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.qib/","/ʕaqb/","/ʕa.qi.ba/","/ʕa.qa.ba/","/ʕaq.qa.ba/","/ʕuqb/","/ʕu.qub/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29831","headword_ar":"عَقْبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in eight places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29832","headword_ar":"عُقْبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in seven places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29833","headword_ar":"عَقَبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awotaAr","text_ar":"اَوْتَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strings for bows or the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K: [see also 1, last quarter:]) n. un. with 3: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are white of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAb","text_ar":"اَطْنَاب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the joints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb; [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabN","text_ar":"عَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being such as are yellow: (Mgh and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESb","text_ar":"عصب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) accord. to IAth, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the two portions of flesh next the back-bone on either side, and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqaAni","text_ar":"سَاقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZiyfaAni","text_ar":"وَظِيفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hind and fore shanks"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are intermingled with the flesh, of any animal; the half of one whereof, divided lengthwise from the other half, is extended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drown out, and trimmed, and cleansed of the flesh, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watar","text_ar":"وَتَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"string for the bow or the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is made thereof; and they are sometimes in the two sides of the camel; but"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properly speaking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is a difference between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSab","text_ar":"عَصَب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqab","text_ar":"عقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the former being such as incline to yellow, whereas the latter incline to white, and are the harder, and firmer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stronger, of the two:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says, on the authority of Aboo-Ziyád, that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqab","text_ar":"عَقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"are [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the two portions of flesh next the back-bone on either side, of the sheep or goat, and of the camel, and of the ox or cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilobaA='N","text_ar":"عِلْبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n29834","headword_ar":"عَقِبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) the latter being a contraction of the former, (Msb,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heel"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being;] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder part of the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being: (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) of the fem. gender: (S, O, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqubN","text_ar":"اَعْقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and [of mult. as well as of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiybN","text_ar":"عَقِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify the same; but MF cites an assertion that this is a word of a bad dialect. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolN liloA^aEoqaAbi mina Aln~aAri","text_ar":"وَيْلٌ لِلْاَعْقَابِ مِنَ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wo to the heels from the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Hell], (O, Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wyl liloEaqibi mn Aln~Ar","text_ar":"ويل لِلْعَقِبِ من النّار"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who to the heel"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], (TA,) occurring in a trad., means wo to him who neglects the washing of the heels in the ablution preparatory to prayer. (O, * Msb, TA. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqibu","text_ar":"عَقِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayoTaAni","text_ar":"الشَّيْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, TA,) or, as some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapu","text_ar":"عُقْبَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$yTAn","text_ar":"الشيطان"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) with damm, (TA,) which is forbidden in prayer, is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The placing the buttocks upon the heels between the two prostrations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is what some term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iqoEaA='u","text_ar":"الاـِقْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, * O, Msb, TA:) so says A'Obeyd: (Msb:) or, accord. to some, this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaving the heels unwashed in the ablution preparatory to prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waTiy^a Aln~aAsu Eaqiba fulaAnK","text_ar":"وَطِيَ النَّاسُ عَقِبَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people trod upon the heel of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people walked after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after, such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa muwaT~aA^u AlEaqibi","text_ar":"هُوَ مُوَطَّاُ العَقِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one whose heel is trodden upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA; *) because of his having command over people, and their being submissive to him: (O:) the latter phrase means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one who has many followers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA: [see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wTA^","text_ar":"وطا"},{"kind":"text","text":":])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a zayodN yaTaA^u Eaqiba","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ زَيْدٌ يَطَاُ عَقِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamorKw","text_ar":"عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"text","text":"primarily signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd came putting his foot in the place of the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of 'Amr every time that the latter raised his foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^ayona Eaqibuka","text_ar":"مِنْ اَيْنَ عَقِبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^ayona","text_ar":"مِنْ اَيْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna Eaqibuka","text_ar":"كَانَ عَقِبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whence camest thou?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whence hast thou come?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa fulaAnN EalaY Eaqibihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ فُلَانٌ عَلَى عَقِبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one returned by the way of his heel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the way that was behind him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence he had come; quickly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~aY EalaY Eaqibihi","text_ar":"وَلَّى عَلَى عَقِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eaqibayohi","text_ar":"عَلَى عَقِبَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receded, from a thing to which he had betaken himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tarud~ahumo EalaY A^aEoqaAbihimo","text_ar":"لَا تَرُدَّهُمْ عَلَى اَعْقَابِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn not thou them back to their former condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"of not emigrating [for the sake of religion]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAluwA murotad~iyna","text_ar":"مَا زَالُوا مُرْتَدِّينَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY A^aEoqaAbihimo","text_ar":"عَلَى اَعْقَابِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in another trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They ceased not to return to infidelity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though they went back wards. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqib","text_ar":"عَقِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEol","text_ar":"نَعْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or sandal] is The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide strap"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that embraces the heel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, in an anom. MS. in my possession.) ―         -b3-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqibu AlbaAbi","text_ar":"عَقِبُ البَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pivot"},{"kind":"text","text":"(generally of wood)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the bottom of the door, turning in a socket in the threshold."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqubN","text_ar":"عُقُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobN","text_ar":"عُقْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobapN","text_ar":"عُقْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobaAnN","text_ar":"عِقْبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibN","text_ar":"عَاقِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, TA,) which signifies, (S, O, Msb, K,) i. e. as signifying, (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but generally as explanatory of this last word, and often as explanatory of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqubN","text_ar":"عُقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobN","text_ar":"عُقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consequence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"result,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"issue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of anything: (S, O, Msb, K, TA:) [and the same words, app. with the exception of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, of subsequence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. [of the first four words is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] of the last"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAqibu","text_ar":"عَوَاقِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence, (S,) it is said in the Kur [xviii. 42], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa xayorN vawaAbFA waxayorN EuqubFA","text_ar":"هُوَ خَيْرٌ ثَوَابًا وَخَيْرٌ عُقُبًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobFA","text_ar":"عُقْبًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different readings, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the best in respect of recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward, and the best in respect of consequence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"result,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"issue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., the consequence of the actions &c. of believers]. (S, O.) And in the same [xci. last verse], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA yaxaAfu EuqobaAhaA","text_ar":"وَلَا يَخَافُ عُقْبَاهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And He feareth not the consequence thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA.) And they said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka fiY Alxayori","text_ar":"لَكَ فِى الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuqobaY","text_ar":"العُقْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAqibapu","text_ar":"العَاقِبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2101},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May the end to thee be in that which is good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may thy case end in good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAfara fiY Eaqibi ramaDaAna","text_ar":"سَافَرَ فِى عَقِبِ رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O, Msb,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He journeyed in the end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter, part, of Ramadán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when Ramadán had almost ended."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu fiY Eaqibi ramaDaAna","text_ar":"جِيْتُ فِى عَقِبِ رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S, O, * Msb, *) with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when there was somewhat remaining of Ramadán."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, O, * Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuka fiY Eaqibi Al$~ahori","text_ar":"جِيْتُكَ فِى عَقِبِ الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY Eaqobihi","text_ar":"فى عَقْبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eaqibihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عَقِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee in the latter part of the month, when ten days of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less, remained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa fiY Eaqibi AlmaraDi","text_ar":"هُوَ فِى عَقِبِ المَرَضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in the state of convalescence in which somewhat remains of the disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^aEoqaAbi","text_ar":"فِى اَعْقَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaraDi","text_ar":"المَرَضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state in which there are some"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Eaqibihi","text_ar":"فِى عَقِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqobihi","text_ar":"عَقْبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at his heel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"close after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a Eaqibahu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ عَقِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a zayodN yaTaA^u Eaqiba EamorKw","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ زَيْدٌ يَطَاُ عَقِبَ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning as expl. above. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw fulaAnK saqoYu A_ibilihimo","text_ar":"بَنُو فُلَانٍ سَقْىُ اـِبِلِهِمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiba baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَقِبَ بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sons of such a one, the watering of their camels is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sons of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a saying mentioned by ISk. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~ayonaA A^aEoqaAba AlfariyDapi taTaw~uEFA","text_ar":"صَلَّيْنَا اَعْقَابَ الفَرِيضَةِ تَطَوُّعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We performed prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by way of supererogation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lh, IF, Msb, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu fiY Eaqibi Al$~ahori","text_ar":"جِيْتُ فِى عَقِبِ الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came after the month had passed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Fárábee, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalafa","text_ar":"خَلَفَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN bEaqibiY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بعَقِبِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed, after me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Er-Rázee says, in the Mukhtár es- Siháh, that he had found no authority in the T nor in the S for the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN Eqba fulaAnK","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ عقبَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiba","text_ar":"عَقِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came after such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"except a similar saying of ISk, cited by Az, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqba","text_ar":"عقبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [But if the word in question be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiba","text_ar":"عَقِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sufficient authorities for its use in this sense have been cited above: though it seems from what here follows that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euquba","text_ar":"عُقُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqoba","text_ar":"عُقْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense is preferable.] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahori","text_ar":"شَهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu fiY Euqobi","text_ar":"جِيْتُ فِى عُقْبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaDaAna","text_ar":"رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqubihi","text_ar":"عُقُبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Euqobihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عُقْبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqubihi","text_ar":"عُقُبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY EuqobaAnihi","text_ar":"فِى عُقْبَانِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came when the whole of the month of Rama- dán had passed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuka Euqoba","text_ar":"جِيْتُكَ عُقْبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaDaAna","text_ar":"رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee at the end of Ramadán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamar~ihi","text_ar":"مَمَرِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu fulaAnFA EalaY Euqobi","text_ar":"جِيْتُ فُلَانًا عَلَى عُقْبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqubihi","text_ar":"عُقُبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqibihi","text_ar":"عَقِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaAnihi","text_ar":"عُقْبَانِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to such a one after he had gone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuka EalaY Euqubi","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُكَ عَلَى عُقُبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiba","text_ar":"عَقِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*Ak","text_ar":"ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*Ak","text_ar":"ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqobi","text_ar":"عَقْبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*Ak","text_ar":"ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaAni","text_ar":"عُقْبَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee after that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quduwmihi","text_ar":"قُدُومِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuhu Euqoba","text_ar":"جِيْتُهُ عُقْبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him after his arrival."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=li fulaAnK","text_ar":"ا=لِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yasotaqiY EalaY Euqobapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَسْتَقِى عَلَى عُقْبَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one draws water after the family of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And MF mentions ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuka EalaY EaAqibihi","text_ar":"جِيْتُكَ عَلَى عَاقِبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee after him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and Aboo-Mis-hal mentions [app. in this sense] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobaAnihi","text_ar":"عِقْبَانِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) also signify The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K,) of a man; (S, O;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children, of the child"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K,) of a man: (S, O:) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as remain after the father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, accord. to some of the lawyers, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children of the daughters"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a man, also]: (Mgh:) of the fem. gender, on the authority of Akh: (S, O:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbN","text_ar":"اَعْقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Eaqiba lahu","text_ar":"لَا عَقِبَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are, no male offspring remaining to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosato lifulaAnK EaAqibapN","text_ar":"لَيْسَتْ لِفُلَانٍ عَاقِبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are, to such a one, no"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'K","text_ar":"شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqobu","text_ar":"عَقْبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqibu $aYo'K","text_ar":"عَقِبُ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whatever it be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that follows, succeeds, comes after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"takes the place of, a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the water of a well, and the blowing of the wind, and the flying of the sand-grouse ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaTaA","text_ar":"القَطَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and the running of a horse. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibN","text_ar":"عَاقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, IF, A, Msb,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or, as As says, each of these, some of the Arabs using the latter form, by way of contraction, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A run after another run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, IF, S, Msb, K,) of a horse: (As, IF, S, Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter, run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (IAar, Msb:) or one says of a courser,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uwo EafowK waEaqibK","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُوْ عَفْوٍ وَعَقِبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a first run, and a subsequent, and more vehement, run:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAbN","text_ar":"عِقَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said in the L to have the first of these meanings: (TA:) or it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as having that meaning: (Ham p. 358:) an ex. of it occurs in the following verse, (Ham, TA,) cited by IAar: (TA:)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yamolaA^u Eayonayoka biAlfinaA='i wayuro\n                      \n                     \n                        Diyka EiqaAbFA A_ino $iy^ota A^awo nazaqaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That would satisfy thine eye by his beauty, in the area before the dwelling, and content thee by run after run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by runs after runs, if thou wilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by lightness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agility"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ham, TA:) [or it may be here an inf. n., (of 3,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on an occasion of being required to perform run after run:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 3, last sentence:)] or, accord. to IAar, the meaning in this instance is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by his owner's making, upon him, warring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warring and plundering, expeditions time after time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) accord. to Kh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EiqaAbN","text_ar":"لَهُ عِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a horse, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has a recovering of strength"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmAm","text_ar":"جمام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAmN","text_ar":"جَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after ceasing to run."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ubi suprà.) ―         -b8-  Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A reply:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying, relating to him who stops, or breaks off, in speech,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo kaAna lahu EaqibN latakal~ama","text_ar":"لَوْ كَانَ لَهُ عَقِبٌ لَتَكَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If he had a reply, assuredly he would have spoken"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b9-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqobapN","text_ar":"عِقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","Mgh","O","K","A","T","ISk","L","IAar","IF","As","Ham"]},{"entry_id":"n29835","headword_ar":"عُقُبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in six places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}